                h3 Interviews
                p 
                    | By analyzing current products, I gained a lot of inspirations. However, I also realized that those "competitors" are mainly 
                    span.highlight designed for every member on the team rather than the manager specifically
                    | . They solve the problem of, in some sense, project/task management and the idea of leadership is weakened.
                p
                    | Therefore, I conducted 5 interviews (
                    span.highlight different industries
                    | ) to get more insights on the idea of "managing a team". I asked both qualitative and quantitative questions and observed how people would lead or manage their teams.
                p Qualitative questions might be: 
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span In what scenario you would use a team management tool?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span How do you evaluate your team status in the work? What feature you value the most?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span How do keep the morale of the team?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Do you prefer a strict or loose management style?
                p Quantitative questions to answer might include:
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span How many team members you would like to work with? What is the maximum number?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span How many projects would be suitable for a team member to work on at a time?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Which factor do you emphasize more: the projects or the members?
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right 
                            span How frequent do you receive notifications from your team members?
                p There were some interesting findings from the interview: 1. People mainly use team management tool in office; 2. They are actually flexible about their management strategies, e.g. Tendencies towards projects and members vary from person to person; 3. People prefer a team with less than 15 people;  4. Quick and effective communication is key to success in their minds.
        .level#section2
