                                |  is used in office rather than a mobile app being used during a business trip.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                | Restricting to 
                                span.highlight people in serious business
                                |  instead of those in schools, sport teams and etc.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                | Prioritizing user needs from 
                                span.highlight managers
                                |  comparing to other team members.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                | Targeting 
                                span.highlight a small-sized team
                                |  with a number of team member smaller than 20 maybe.
                h3 Product Goals
                p For further guidance, I wrote a creative brief.
                .board
                    h3.smaller Creative Brief Excerpt
                    h4 Who are the target audiences and their priorities?
                    p
                        | Teams of business people including 
                        b manager
                        | , 
                        b assistant
                        |  and 
                        b other members
                        | . The product prioritizes team manager first.
                    h4 What makes our team management tool unique?
                    p 
                        | There are basically three factors. 1. 
                        b Holistic views
                        | —managers are able get an immediate impression of members/projects status; 2. 
                        b Multiple styles
                        | —the tool could be easily adapted to different leadership styles; 3. 
                        b Teammates' interactions
                        | —the tool provides multiple ways for team members to share, communicate or collaborate.
                    h4 What personality does the tool want to project to the audience?
                    p Clear, professional, effective, interesting and flexible.
                p
                    | Therefore, I easily got my goal for the product: 
                    span.highlight to design a desktop version of professional team management tool that facilitate a manager's work within a small team
                    | .
        .level#section3
            .container
                h2 EXPLORING AND ANALYZING
                .sep.taller
                h3 Persona
                p
                    | I then considered the questions above from the lens of our main customer: Larry Roberts. The persona could be described as follow:
                .board
                    h3.smaller Manager Persona
                    h4 Brief Introduction
                    p Larry Roberts, 35, is a manager in a consulting service company. He is responsible for a team consists of 12 consultants and 1 team assistant. These consultants are assigned to different customer projects. One project may be handled by one or multiple consultants.
                    h4 Management Behaviours
                    p 1. Track the status of all the projects in his team, in terms of timeline, budget, and quality, etc. 2. Understand who is doing what. 3. Build a learning organization, which facilitates knowledge sharing and collaboration. 4. Keep the morale. 5. Process the leave requests, shopping requests, and expense reports from team members.
                h3 User Needs
                p
                    | According to the persona, I listed out 5 users needs and placed them within a self-made coordinating system. The x-axis represents 
                    span.highlight importance or motivation
                    |  of the need from low to high while the y-axis represents  
                    span.highlight frequency
                    |  of need being accomplished.
        .level.level--humming-bird
