                h3 Assumption
                p Therefore, managers would take the following factors into consideration when choosing a team management tool:
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                b Clarity
                                |—Members, projects and their relations must be clear and easy to navigate through.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                b Professionalism
                                |—Data attributes related to projects and members must be professional and useful in his business.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                b Efficiency
                                |—Tasks such as assigning projects to members or processing requests and reports should be accomplished intuitively and easily.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                b Interaction
                                |—System should provide chances for members to interact with each other, e.g. learning organization and discussion board.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span
                                b Flexibility
                                |—Managers are able to adjust their management strategies based on personal interest or team status, e.g. morale.
                h3 Information Architecture
                p
                    | I separated information into two main categories: things a manager could 
                    span.highlight actively create and browse
                    | , and things a manager would 
                    span.highlight passively receive and process
                    | .
                p The first category includes project lists, member lists, learning organizations, statistics and team building activities. The second is mainly message system, encompassing requests, reports and other notifications.
