                h2 IDEATION
                .sep.taller
                h3 1. Maximize Clarity
                p
                    | The system organizes information into modules and builds the navigation along them. In this regards, maximized clarity was achieved with system consistently following the information architecture mentioned before or in other words, 
                    span.highlight a reasonable hierarchy
                    | . 
                h3 2. Enhance Professionalism
                p
                    | A product speaks for itself with more 
                    span.highlight complete and reliable data
                    | . So does this team management tool. My design was to provide as much accurate data as possible including numbers, trendings, times, etc. I put much emphasis on numbers especially because that's the effective way in which a manager would trust a system.
                img(data-src="assets/img/tmt/tmt-sketches-1.jpg").lazyload.img--result
                h3 3. Ensure Efficiency
                p
                    | Manipulations of the tools should be highly effective. I wanted to use the 
                    span.highlight button-modal interaction
                    |  to give a more immersive experience. Meanwhile, the way a manager 
                    span.highlight deals with requests and reports
                    |  would be intuitive. Plus, I provided 
                    span.highlight filtering and sorting
                    |  functions for managers to compare and thus get better insights.
                h3 4. Provide Interactions
                p
                    | Providing Interactions among team members is the key to a successful team. There are several ways to do so:  1. The tool contains 
                    span.highlight a variety of approaches
                    |  to group learning and discussions. 2. Communication through the tool is 
                    span.highlight fast
                    |  and 
                    span.highlight in-time. 
                p
                    | In this case, I designed multiple ways where a team could communicate—different kinds of organizations, requests and reports, and message/notifications system directly.
                h3 5. Build Your Own Leadership
                p
                    | A manager builds his leadership in his own manner, either in strict or loose way. Our design should be prepared for each situation. First, our dashboard should include a 
                    span.highlight customization functionality
                    | . Manager would easily select information that is needed for him. Second, the system should contain a 
                    span.highlight rewarding or punishment
                    |  system. Third, managers are able to control their authorities by 
                    span.highlight assigning and withdrawing roles
                    |  to a team member. In this way, 
                    span.highlight a flexible management
                    |  is achieved.
