                h2 ASSESSMENT
                .sep
                p In the end, I used heuristic evaluations to briefly judge this team management tool. I felt like the design was far from success. Apart from the strengths, it has the following weaknesses.
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Different modules have little characteristics to distinguish themselves one from the other.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Message system is a little bit chaotic since it exists both in main and side navigation bars.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span The tool lacks error prevention and correction.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span The process of customization has not being touched.
                p Then I would continue to iterate and refine the experience. Looking forward, I would start exploring how to integrate the experience into other contexts. For instance, I would revamp the tool towards team assistant or other team members. Also, I would help the tool get deployed to other platforms such as tablets or mobile phones so that more people within more scenarios would use it.
